label: Boys in school (count)
codebookDescription: Number of boys in the school

label: Diagnostic test done in school
definition: Whether each school was examined with CCA test, KK test or both
codebookDescription: Whether each school was examined with CCA test, KK test or both

label: Girls in school (count)
codebookDescription: Number of girls in the school

label: School ID
codebookDescription: Identity code for each school

label: School based treatments in previous 12 months (count)
definition: Numeric to indicate number of treatments in last 12 months at school. PZQ= praziquantel (anti-schistosomal drug); ALB= albendazole (deworming drug)
codebookDescription: Numeric to indicate number of treatments in last 12 months at school. PZQ= praziquantel (anti-schistosomal drug); ALB= albendazole (deworming drug)

label: School eco-epidemiological risk zone
definition: S. mansoni prevalence was assessed in several eco-epidemiological risk zones with either high or low risk of schistosomiasis.
codebookDescription: Eco-epidemiological risk zone of school

label: Sentinel site
definition: This is a flag to indicate whether the school was a sentinel site (where monitoring of the national schistosomiasis control program had previously taken place) or not
codebookDescription: Flag to indicate whether the school is a sentinel site or not

label: Water source type within 5km of school
definition: Presence or absence of different types of sources of water within 5km of the school

label: Irrigation canal
parentLabel: Water source type within 5km of school

label: Lake
parentLabel: Water source type within 5km of school
codebookDescription: Flags to indicate presence or absence of different types of sources of water within 5km of the school

label: Marsh or swamp
parentLabel: Water source type within 5km of school

label: Other water source
parentLabel: Water source type within 5km of school

label: Pond
parentLabel: Water source type within 5km of school

label: Ricefield
parentLabel: Water source type within 5km of school

label: River
parentLabel: Water source type within 5km of school

label: Age
codebookDescription: Age of each pupil in years

label: Sex
codebookDescription: Sex of each pupil

label: Hookworm, by microscopy
definition: Binary flag to indicate Ancylostomatoidea (Hookworm) infection through egg detection in Kato-Katz test
codebookDescription: Binary flag to indicate Ankylo infection through egg detection in KK

label: Sample mean Hookworm, by microscopy
definition: Mean eggs per gram (epg) of Ancylostomatoidea (Hookworm) where two slides were recorded, or the single observation where only one slide was recorded
codebookDescription: Average epg of Ankylo where two slides were recorded, or the single observation where only one slide was recorded

label: Ascaris lumbricoides, by microscopy
definition: Binary flag to indicate Ascaris infection through egg detection in Kato-Katz test
codebookDescription: Binary flag to indicate Ascaris infection through egg detection in KK

label: Sample mean Ascaris lumbricoides, by microscopy
definition: Mean eggs per gram (epg) of Ascaris where two slides were recorded, or the single observation where only one slide was recorded
codebookDescription: Average epg of Ascaris where two slides were recorded, or the single observation where only one slide was recorded

label: Schistosoma mansoni, by CCA result
definition: Results of Circulating Cathodic Antigen (CCA) test
codebookDescription: Results of CCA test

label: Sample mean Schistosoma mansoni, by microscopy
definition: Mean eggs per gram (epg) of S.mansoni where two slides were recorded, or the single observation where only one slide was recorded
codebookDescription: Average epg of S.mansoni where two slides were recorded, or the single observation where only one slide was recorded

label: Schistosoma mansoni, by microscopy
definition: Binary flag to indicate S.mansoni infection through egg detection in Kato-Katz test
codebookDescription: Binary flag to indicate S.mansoni  infection through egg detection in KK

label: Schistosoma mansoni, by microscopy field decision
definition: Decision made in the field of whether individual was positive for mansoni by Kato-Katz. Doesn't always match with the egg info.
codebookDescription: Decision made in the field of whether individual was positive for mansoni by KK. Doesn't always match with the egg info.

label: Schistosoma mansoni, by CCA
definition: Binary flag to indicate S.mansoni infection through Circulating Cathodic Antigen (CCA) test with trace counted as postive
codebookDescription: Binary flag to indicate S.mansoni infection through CCA with trace counted as postive

label: Sample mean Trichuris trichuria, by microscopy
definition: Mean eggs per gram (epg) of Trichuris where two slides were recorded, or the single observation where only one slide was recorded
codebookDescription: Average egg of Trichuris where two slides were recorded, or the single observation where only one slide was recorded

label: Trichuris trichiura, by microscopy
definition: Binary flag to indicate Trichuris infection through egg detection in Kato-Katz test
codebookDescription: Binary flag to indicate Trichuris infection through egg detection in KK

label: Microhematuria
codebookDescription: Result of haematuria test
